==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*ders-'', from Indo-European ''*dhers-''.  Cognate with Old Frisian ''dūra'' (Frisian [[doare]]), Old High German [[giturran]], Old Saxon [[gidurran]]; and with Greek [[θαρσειν]] ‘be bold’.

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/'dʊr:an/}}

